Hello
I am 30 years old.
I started doing coke at 20 years old.
I never took it every day, it wasn't super addictive.
I used to take it 1 or 2 times a month at most, but for about 6 months or even a year now, I can control myself when I drink alcohol.
Even though I promised myself I wouldn't go looking for some shnouf before, after 2 or 3 glasses I start to get warm and think, "Well, we only have one life, it's parti-iiii" and it's impossible to control myself, I'm too eager to take more.
So here, I know the problem is alcohol at its core, but it's crazy impossible to stop in the family, among friends for the apero, etc.
Has anyone this problem?
Thank you
stop drinking and the problem will be solved
sometimes one has to be violent to oneself to stop ...
have you at least talked to your family doctor about it?
seeing an addict could do you good, especially to "evaluate" your consumption
