Good morning to you Cllaude271. To begin with, I do not take LSD.
It happens that I take speed (amphetamine) or drink alcohol but not LSD, ketamine, or anything else.
I think you should simply see another doctor or a toxicologist (I don't know if that's the exact term)
If after 5 months you still experience this kind of "side effect," it's really bad.
So without wanting to alarm you, you should see a toxicologist who, I think, will prescribe an emergency treatment or antidotes.
Otherwise there are green numbers or specialized forums. Good continuation. Peace
Hello Claude271,
Having been through the state you describe many times (due to a mix of chatterboxes, micropoints, taz, keta, in short, everything that passed through there),
If I can give you a piece of advice, it's simply to tell yourself that all of this is just psychological.
In short, the more you stress about these states, the worse they will get.
A very simple thing to do in such cases is to take deep breaths, breathe gently, and settle in a place where you feel safe, and not too close to the walls (yes, sometimes you might feel like they are closing in on you).
After several months following a dose, especially when you mix them, you can experience effects, particularly after a sudden stop of the substances.
Don't worry, it's just a matter of time.
But as Claude532 said, consulting a psychiatrist can also help you get rid of those voices that clutter your head.
Stay strong and stay positive.
Thank you both for your responses
